To conserve the short-circiuting behavior of the operators, you can split them into if statements:

```
int main()
{
  int i = 1, j = 1, k = 0, m;
  ++i;
  if (i == 0) {
    ++j;
    if (j != 0) {
      ++k;
      if (k == 0) {
        m = 0;
      } else {
        m = 1;
      }
    } else {
